HEADWORD: Lintel
<hw>Lin"tel</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n"t⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>lintel</ets>, F. <ets>linteau</ets>, LL. <ets>lintellus</ets>, for
<ets>limitellus</ets>, a dim. fr. L. <ets>limes</ets> limit. See
<er>Limit</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A horizontal member
spanning an opening, and carrying the superincumbent weight by means of
its strength in resisting crosswise fracture.</def>⟦br⟧
